\subsection{Method \code{add_order()}}{
Place a Stop Order

Places a stop order (limit or market) that triggers when the stop
price is reached. For limit stop orders, both \code{price} and \code{size} are
required. For market stop orders, either \code{size} or \code{funds} must be
specified (but not both), and \code{price} must not be set.
\subsection{Workflow}{
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Validation}: Checks \code{type}, \code{side}, and \code{symbol} format; enforces
type-specific parameter constraints (e.g., \code{price} required for limit,
\code{funds}/\code{size} mutual exclusivity for market).
\item \strong{Body Construction}: Assembles the request body with required and
optional parameters, converting numerics to character strings as needed.
\item \strong{Request}: Authenticated POST to the stop order endpoint.
\item \strong{Parsing}: Returns a \code{data.table} with the assigned \code{order_id} and \code{client_oid}.
}
}

\subsection{API Endpoint}{

\verb{POST https://api.kucoin.com/api/v1/stop-order}
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\href{https://www.kucoin.com/docs-new/rest/spot-trading/orders/add-stop-order}{KuCoin Add Stop Order}

Verified: 2026-02-01
}

\subsection{Automated Trading Usage}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Stop-Loss}: Place a sell stop order below your entry price to automatically exit a losing position.
\item \strong{Breakout Entry}: Place a buy stop order above resistance to enter on a confirmed breakout.
\item \strong{Risk Management}: Combine with \code{timeInForce = "GTT"} and \code{cancelAfter} to auto-expire stale stop orders.
}
}

