\subsection{Method \code{get_order_by_client_oid()}}{
Get Stop Order by Client OID

Retrieves stop order details using the client-assigned order ID and symbol.
May return multiple results if the same \code{clientOid} was used across different orders.
\subsection{Workflow}{
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Request}: Authenticated GET with \code{clientOid} and \code{symbol} as query parameters.
\item \strong{Parsing}: If multiple orders match, returns a multi-row \code{data.table};
otherwise returns a single-row \code{data.table}.
}
}

\subsection{API Endpoint}{

\verb{GET https://api.kucoin.com/api/v1/stop-order/queryOrderByClientOid}
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\href{https://www.kucoin.com/docs-new/rest/spot-trading/get-stop-order-by-clientoid}{KuCoin Get Stop Order By ClientOid}

Verified: 2026-02-01
}

\subsection{Automated Trading Usage}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Client-Side Lookup}: Query stop orders using your own identifiers without persisting KuCoin IDs.
\item \strong{Order Reconciliation}: Verify that a stop order with a given client OID exists and check its parameters.
\item \strong{Deduplication Check}: Before placing a new stop order, check if one with the same client OID already exists.
}
}

