\subsection{Method \code{get_order_list()}}{
Get Stop Order List

Retrieves a paginated list of stop orders with optional filtering by symbol,
side, type, and time range. Returns all matching stop orders as a \code{data.table}.
\subsection{Workflow}{
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Request}: Authenticated GET with optional query parameters for filtering and pagination.
\item \strong{Parsing}: Extracts the \code{items} array from the paginated response and
binds rows into a \code{data.table}. Returns an empty \code{data.table} if no orders match.
}
}

\subsection{API Endpoint}{

\verb{GET https://api.kucoin.com/api/v1/stop-order}
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\href{https://www.kucoin.com/docs-new/rest/spot-trading/orders/get-stop-orders-list}{KuCoin Get Stop Order List}

Verified: 2026-02-01
}

\subsection{Automated Trading Usage}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Portfolio Monitoring}: Periodically poll active stop orders to maintain an accurate view of pending triggers.
\item \strong{Reconciliation}: Compare local order state with exchange state on bot startup or after reconnection.
\item \strong{Reporting}: Retrieve historical stop orders filtered by time range for performance analysis.
}
}

\subsection{curl}{

\if{html}{\out{<div class="sourceCode">}}\preformatted{curl --location --request GET 'https://api.kucoin.com/api/v1/stop-order?symbol=BTC-USDT&side=sell&pageSize=50&currentPage=1' \\
